       np->rxopt.bits.rxinfo || np->rxopt.bits.rxoinfo ||
       np->rxopt.bits.rxhlim || np->rxopt.bits.rxohlim) {
       atomic_inc(&skb->users);
       ireq->pktopts = skb;
   }
   ```
   The code copies relevant fields from the parsed options (`tcp_opt`) and the packet (`skb`) into the new request socket (`req`). It also increments the reference count of the `skb` if certain options are accepted, ensuring that the `skb` remains valid as long as the request socket is in use.

3. **Security Checks**:
   ```c
   if (security_inet_conn_request(sk, skb, req))
       goto out_free;
   ```
   Security checks are performed before proceeding further, which can help prevent malicious packets from causing issues.

4. **Initialization of New Socket Options**:
   ```c
   ireq->snd_wscale    = tcp_opt.snd_wscale;
   ireq->sack_ok       = tcp_opt.sack_ok;
   ireq->wscale_ok     = tcp_opt.wscale_ok;
   ireq->tstamp_ok     = tcp_opt.saw_tstamp;
