   treq->snt_synack.v64= 0;
   treq->rcv_isn = ntohl(th->seq) - 1;
   treq->snt_isn = cookie;
   ```
   The new socket's options are initialized based on the parsed options (`tcp_opt`), ensuring that the new socket has its own set of options.

5. **Handling Destination Entry**:
   ```c
   dst = ip6_dst_lookup_flow(sk, &fl6, final_p);
   if (IS_ERR(dst))
       goto out_free;
   ```
   The destination entry (`dst`) is looked up and checked for errors. This ensures that the new socket has a valid destination entry.

